Sentencas: Yttrium-doped barium zirconate (Y:BaZrO3, BZY) thin films were prepared using pulsed laser deposition (PLD) on MgO substrates at 700 degrees C by varying the ambient oxygen pressure.
Titulo: Influence of background oxygen pressure on film properties of pulsed laser deposited Y:BaZrO3

Sentencas: The microstructure and electrical properties were then investigated using transmission electron microscopy and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Influence of background oxygen pressure on film properties of pulsed laser deposited Y:BaZrO3

Sentencas: Dense, well-crystallized BZY films were produced at ambient oxygen pressures (P-amb,P-o2) of <= 6.67 Pa.
Titulo: Influence of background oxygen pressure on film properties of pulsed laser deposited Y:BaZrO3

Sentencas: At P-amb,P- (2)(o) = 13.3 Pa, conical amorphous defects and porous microstructures were observed in the films.
Titulo: Influence of background oxygen pressure on film properties of pulsed laser deposited Y:BaZrO3

Sentencas: The conductivity of PLD BZY prepared at P-amb,P-o2 <= 13.3 Pa was measured to be close to that of reference polycrystalline BZY films, and the grain-boundary properties governed the overall ion conduction, with nano-grains being covered by the space charge depletion zones.
Titulo: Influence of background oxygen pressure on film properties of pulsed laser deposited Y:BaZrO3

Sentencas: At P-amb,P-o2 >= 13.3 Pa, microstructural defects significantly degraded the electrical properties.
Titulo: Influence of background oxygen pressure on film properties of pulsed laser deposited Y:BaZrO3
